            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2240-Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>avocado<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways and remove the stone<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> using a teaspoon</p>\n<p>Scoop the <strong>avocado</strong> out of the skin<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> using a spoon and add it to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>juice</strong> of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lime</strong></p>\n<p>Blitz until smooth, then stir through the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> with 3/4 of the<strong> chopped onion</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>coriander</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>chunky guacamole</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
